I'm sure we'll make a late surge to claim 4th but that isn't good enough for Arsenal fans anymore. Wenger out, Gazidis out, Kroenke out.

        • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

          @hasan- Oh I don't think Diaby is our long-term defensive midfielder solution by any stretch. I think we need to buy someone for that role. But while Flamini is playing so bad, and in the absence of a quality defensive midfielder, I think Diaby should have a shot. Not as a defensive midfielder per se but a sitting midfielder who acts as a road block in front of the defence a la Gustavo/Carvalho/Matic but with the added ability to do a rangy run forward. Hopefully he doesn't do too many of those against the big teams because essentially what you need in those games is a barrier to stop players like Hazard dancing past defensively-inept midfielders. I don't think Diaby has the dedication or concentration to do for us what Matic does for Chelsea but who at our club does?
